      "span_text": "Frozen OCT-embedded GRMD samples were sectioned at 10 mm, and Picosirius red staining was performed as previously described. Briefly, sections were fixed in 4% paraformaldehyde for 10 minutes, rinsed, air dried, stained for 1 hour in 0.1% (wt/vol) Sirius red (Sigma-Aldrich), dissolved in saturated aqueous picric acid (Sigma-Aldrich), washed in 2 changes of 0.5% acetic acid, dehydrated in 3 changes of 100% ethanol, cleared with Citra Solv, and mounted with Cytoseal."
